Yobe State Government has reviewed the curfew time by one hour from 12 midnight to 6.00am as against 11.00pm to 6.00am. A statement by the Special Adviser to Governor Mai Mala Buni on Security, Rtd Brig. Gen. Dahiru Abdulsalam stated that the review will affect all the 17 Local Government Areas in the state. The statement also explained that the review was done in consideration of the improvement of the security situation in the state. The statement, however, warned that the review does not affect inter local government area movement. The statement reads in part: “Sequel to a review of the prevalent security situation across the state and the consequential improvement in the security situation, Governor Buni has approved an adjustment of the night curfew time.   Kano lawmaker shares N150m as Ramadan palliatives     Muslims urged to rededicate lives     A gloomy picture of unending petrol crisis   “Night curfew time is now to commence from 12:00 midnight to 06:00am. The adjustment is for activities within various towns in all the 17 local government areas of the state. “The adjustment is for activities within various towns in all the 17 Local Government Areas of the State.“The review does not affect inter local government area movements. The existing restriction of movement through security checkpoints is still in force. “The existing restriction of movement through security checkpoints is still in force. “Muslim adherents that wish to participate in late night Tahajjud prayers in this holy month of Ramadan are free to do so. All security and law enforcement agencies are requested to kindly take note of this development,” Brig. Gen. Abdulsalam said.